  "text": "If k = 1 we have a block equality and this is then trivial, [CITATION_1] , Corollary 2.8. We may then assume k ≥ 2, which implies w = w(B t ) > 0. Also we let ρ denote the core of the block B t so it is a t-core. We keep this notation in the following.",
